HEADWORD: Inducible
<hw>In*du"ci*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Capable of being induced, caused, or made to take place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Obtainable by induction; derivable;
inferable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Induct</ent>⟦br⟧
